1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,044
- [tense music playing]
- My real name is Hasan Wadi.

2
00:00:03,128 --> 00:00:06,256
[Datu Rahman] <i>I was one</i>
<i>of Colonel Napoleon Marcelino's men.</i>

3
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:08,967
Colonel Marcelino has been dead
for a long time.

4
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:09,884
But I feel that

5
00:00:09,968 --> 00:00:13,471
the system he built is still moving.

6
00:00:14,055 --> 00:00:15,056
What are you looking for?

7
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:16,141
Is this what you're looking for?

8
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:17,934
[Teresa] <i>I didn't know you kept that.</i>

9
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:20,395
[Marcus] <i>I just feel like Gabriel's</i>
<i>with me when I have this.</i>

10
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:24,232
Gabriel's lucky to have
an older brother like you.

11
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:27,235
[Marcus] <i>The authorities</i>
<i>said it was an accident.</i>

12
00:00:27,318 --> 00:00:28,486
<i>But was it really an accident?</i>

13
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:30,030
<i>Did you blow up the ship?</i>

14
00:00:30,113 --> 00:00:33,742
<i>Were you the reason my brother died?</i>

15
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:34,993
[Lara] <i>Why are we</i>
<i>involving children in this?</i>

16
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,286
[Felix] <i>Don't you ever say that.</i>

17
00:00:36,369 --> 00:00:37,787
Do you know what could happen to you

18
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:39,372
- [Lara] What--
- if the General hears this?

19
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:40,749
- Listen to me!
- Stop it!

20
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:43,376
- [Lara] <i>My father is not God!</i>
- But I'm scared of him.

21
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:48,673
[Felix] <i>So if you want to live,</i>
<i>don't let him hear your doubts!</i>

22
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:50,800
[Sitti] Jalil, wait!

23
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,385
I want to come with you.

24
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:54,262
[Aminah] <i>She doesn't have</i>
<i>her parents anymore.</i>

25
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:57,849
<i>Maybe you could take her with you.</i>

26
00:00:57,932 --> 00:00:58,975
[Aminah sniffs]

27
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:02,103
[Azuelo] <i>Because of you,</i>
<i>the public's trust</i>

28
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:04,022
<i>in the police force</i>
<i>is gradually returning.</i>

29
00:01:04,105 --> 00:01:08,568
Thank you, Reyes, for reminding me
why I entered this line of work.

30
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:11,279
[Azuelo] <i>I want my children</i>
<i>and my future grandchildren</i>

31
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:13,031
<i>to live in a safe world.</i>

32
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:16,785
[Teresa] <i>Marcus told me</i>
<i>it was Allan who brought your father.</i>

33
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:21,414
Lately, I've been thinking
about Gabriel because of Allan.

34
00:01:21,498 --> 00:01:23,958
[Teresa] <i>I see my youngest child in him.</i>

35
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,878
[Solares] <i>Prepare yourselves.</i>
<i>Over the next few days,</i>

36
00:01:26,961 --> 00:01:28,630
they'll release the evidence
pointing to you.

37
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:31,466
[Mardrigal] <i>We won't forget</i>
<i>your sacrifices.</i>

38
00:01:31,549 --> 00:01:32,842
If our suspicions are correct…

39
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:36,012
[Espina] <i>The chaos that happened</i>
<i>due to proliferation of illegal weapons</i>

40
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:38,264
- <i>was all planned.</i>
- [Marcus] <i>But for what?</i>

41
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:39,974
What do they gain by causing trouble?

42
00:01:40,058 --> 00:01:42,101
How does the syndicate benefit

43
00:01:42,185 --> 00:01:44,979
if they don't make money
from those weapons?

44
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,941
[Lara] <i>They're working together,</i>
<i>and they're figuring things out.</i>

45
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:49,818
They only have suspicions.

46
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:52,946
What if they get evidence
and discover the truth?

47
00:01:53,029 --> 00:01:55,115
Then we'll kill them.

48
00:01:55,198 --> 00:01:57,492
[intense music playing]

49
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:06,084
[mysterious theme music playing]

50
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:15,218
IBRAHIM
HALAL EATERY

51
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:17,053
[Sitti] We were having fun.

52
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:20,265
Jamilah was even playing with us.

53
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:21,182
[melancholic music playing]

54
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:22,475
But then… [sobbing softly]

55
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:25,645
…there was a loud bang.

56
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:27,772
[crying softly]

57
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:29,941
[Sitti] That's when it became messy.

58
00:02:30,024 --> 00:02:32,610
We were so scared.

59
00:02:33,194 --> 00:02:35,947
Even when the bad guys were gone,

60
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:38,908
it felt like there was still trouble.

61
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:44,247
[somber music playing]

62
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:49,586
But luckily,

63
00:02:50,086 --> 00:02:54,924
Jalil arrived. He saved our island.

64
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:56,593
[gentle music playing]

65
00:02:56,676 --> 00:03:02,223
Auntie Aminah said
the bad guys won't come back.

66
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:04,475
And that's all because of Jalil!

67
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:06,269
[Norhana chuckling]

68
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:07,854
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

69
00:03:07,937 --> 00:03:08,980
Thank you, Allah.

70
00:03:09,063 --> 00:03:10,189
[Norhana sobs]

71
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:12,901
It's good that your island
is fine and well, Sitti.

72
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,111
[Rashid, in Arabic] God willing.

73
00:03:15,194 --> 00:03:17,989
I hope the peace continues on your island.

74
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,950
And everything here
will become peaceful, too.

75
00:03:26,539 --> 00:03:27,624
[Jamilah] Isn't that right, Sitti?

76
00:03:27,707 --> 00:03:30,543
For every hardship, there comes comfort.

77
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:32,962
Allah will not abandon us.

78
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:36,174
- Right, Sitti?
- Yes, Jamilah!

79
00:03:36,257 --> 00:03:37,759
[all laughing softly]

80
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:48,603
[melancholic music playing]

81
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:54,525
[Ahmad] <i>Datu Rahman.</i>

82
00:03:55,693 --> 00:03:57,987
You've already escaped,

83
00:03:58,655 --> 00:03:59,781
went into hiding,

84
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:02,242
detached yourself from the syndicate,

85
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:04,244
but they followed you.

86
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:07,538
They chased you because of your misdeed.

87
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,333
They killed people

88
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,460
to get you.

89
00:04:14,629 --> 00:04:18,299
Brother, you have great intentions.

90
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,177
You don't have to feel guilty

91
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:24,013
for what happened
to our brothers and sisters.

92
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:25,974
[Ahmad] <i>It was destiny.</i>

93
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,142
<i>They're martyrs.</i>

94
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:35,650
[melancholic music continues]

95
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:45,827
[Ahmad] <i>Datu Rahman.</i>

96
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:49,247
About our secret…

97
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,000
I want you to know…

98
00:04:53,084 --> 00:04:56,379
Allah's Word is a witness.

99
00:04:58,047 --> 00:05:02,385
It is best that you tell that
to your children.

100
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,263
Confess to them.

101
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:07,056
[Ahmad] <i>Be true to them.</i>

102
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:10,518
[melancholic music continues]

103
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:16,941
[Ahmad, in English] <i>Brother…</i>

104
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:23,031
<i>Jalil is risking his life</i>
<i>to clear your name.</i>

105
00:05:25,074 --> 00:05:26,701
[Ahmad] You have to trust him.

106
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:28,453
Trust in Allah, brother.

107
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:31,998
Allah! No one can withhold
what Thou givest

108
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:33,374
or give what Thou withholdest,

109
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,501
and the riches cannot avail
a wealthy person with Thee.

110
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:39,922
Brother.

111
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:44,385
Let us live in truth.

112
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,268
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

113
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:54,228
[in Arabic] And upon you be peace.

114
00:05:57,815 --> 00:06:03,071
[melancholic music continues]

115
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:17,627
[puzzling music playing]

116
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:28,262
Their IP's masked, sir.

117
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:31,933
They're using multi-layered
VPN and TOR nodes.

118
00:06:32,016 --> 00:06:33,684
Looks like this will take us a while.

119
00:06:34,852 --> 00:06:35,978
But I promise you, sir.

120
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:39,524
I won't stop until I find
that Uncle Tony guy.

121
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:42,276
Thank you. Just keep me updated, Buster.

122
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,528
[in English] Copy, sir.

123
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:46,489
- [computer beeping]
- [phone buzzing]

124
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:50,910
TERESA: GO HOME EARLY, SON
I COOKED DINNER

125
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:07,552
Reyes. Why are you still here?

126
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:11,264
I'm waiting for the taxi.
I couldn't drive.

127
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,850
Didn't Doc Teresa prepare dinner?

128
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,017
You might be late.

129
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:16,644
She invited you?

130
00:07:17,145 --> 00:07:18,104
Yeah.

131
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:20,064
[gentle music playing]

132
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:21,732
You should just ride with me.

133
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,359
Let's go.

134
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:25,236
Okay.

135
00:07:30,324 --> 00:07:31,784
[car engine starts]

136
00:07:34,328 --> 00:07:41,002
[gentle music playing]

137
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:46,591
Isn't it nice?

138
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:49,385
Sir Marcus and Agent Espina
are finally getting along.

139
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:53,014
I mean, on our first day in TFA,
they're already fighting.

140
00:07:53,097 --> 00:07:56,058
They almost strangled each other
like cats and dogs.

141
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:59,270
Now, they even finish
each others' sentences.

142
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:02,231
Is this their enemies to lovers arc?

143
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:03,441
[laughing]

144
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:05,359
- I meant friends. Friends.
- Friends.

145
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:08,070
Well, it's cute.
It's like they're brothers.

146
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:10,198
That's how our job really is.

147
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:13,367
It's normal to be hostile
in the beginning,

148
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:15,536
but once you've been together in battle,

149
00:08:16,245 --> 00:08:17,663
once you get to know each other more,

150
00:08:18,372 --> 00:08:19,582
that builds trust.

151
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:22,627
Right. Trust is earned.

152
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:26,172
Especially now. We don't know
who our enemy is.

153
00:08:26,255 --> 00:08:32,929
[pensive music]

154
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:45,608
[Usman] <i>I can't lie to Marcus.</i>

155
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,610
Why don't we just tell him the truth?

156
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:48,945
You want the same thing, after all.

157
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:50,988
He is not part of this mission.

158
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,699
Even so, I shouldn't be lying--

159
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,326
[Espina] You're not lying to him.

160
00:08:55,409 --> 00:08:58,371
You're just not telling him
everything you know.

161
00:08:58,955 --> 00:09:00,790
Yes, it is possible
that he is not corrupt.

162
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:02,500
It's possible he wasn't complicit

163
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:04,585
with the people who destroyed our island.

164
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:06,796
But those people still used him.

165
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:11,425
So I hope you can understand
why I can't just trust him.

166
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,979
Why did you get into this line of work?

167
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:26,065
Because…

168
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:28,901
I want to help the underprivileged.

169
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:30,278
We're the same.

170
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:33,322
I started wanting to help others when…

171
00:09:34,031 --> 00:09:35,408
I lost my brother.

172
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:40,580
Gabriel?

173
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:42,707
[Marcus chuckles softly]

174
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:45,751
So my mother also told you
about my brother?

175
00:09:46,335 --> 00:09:47,712
Yes, she mentioned it.

176
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:50,423
How are you?

177
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,342
Are you still affected…

178
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:54,969
by his loss?

179
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:00,808
Of course.

180
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:06,105
Sometimes, I wonder why
he was the one who disappeared.

181
00:10:07,857 --> 00:10:10,026
They should've taken me instead, you know?

182
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:13,654
But I decided

183
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:16,282
my life needs to have meaning.

184
00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:20,244
I won't let my brother's disappearance
go to waste.

185
00:10:20,328 --> 00:10:24,332
[somber music playing]

186
00:10:29,253 --> 00:10:30,379
You're being dramatic.

187
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:33,591
[Marcus chuckles softly]

188
00:10:33,674 --> 00:10:35,176
You're annoying. [chuckles]

189
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:41,432
But I think, your brother,
wherever he is now…

190
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:43,934
he's proud of you.

191
00:10:45,353 --> 00:10:46,354
[Marcus scoffs]

192
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,522
I hope so.

193
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,360
But thank you.

194
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:58,783
[somber music continues]

195
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:04,622
They're starting to catch on, Dad.

196
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,749
Before, our problem was only Agent Reyes,

197
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:10,294
but now, even Major Espina
could be a big problem.

198
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:13,339
[in English] And-- And they're working
with each other, I'm sure of it.

199
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:17,676
[unsettling music playing]

200
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:22,723
Lara…

201
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,395
Did you know about this?

202
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:41,158
[tense music stirring]

203
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:43,202
[in English] Tell me the truth, Lara!

204
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:47,039
[Carillo] Did you know about that?!

205
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:53,295
[yelling] Answer me!

206
00:11:56,674 --> 00:11:57,883
Yes.

207
00:11:57,967 --> 00:11:59,385
- [Carillo] Argh!
- [Lara gasps softly]

208
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:01,303
[Lara breathes heavily]

209
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:06,183
[foreboding music playing]

210
00:12:15,192 --> 00:12:17,778
Oh? You're here.

211
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,655
Did you arrive together?

212
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:23,367
Ah, yeah. I tagged along with him.

213
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:26,662
Really? That's good, then.
Saved up on the gas.

214
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:27,997
[Marcus] What's with this all of a sudden?

215
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,498
[Teresa chuckles]

216
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:32,209
Wait, you already removed the bandage?

217
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:34,420
- Does it not hurt anymore?
- [Marcus sighs]

218
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:35,838
It's fine.

219
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:38,048
My… My doctor's amazing after all.

220
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:40,009
Oh, enough with the flattery.

221
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:42,636
- Good evening, ma'am.
- [Teresa] Allan!

222
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,763
Uh, what happened to your face?

223
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:49,518
Ah… It's nothing. Just a scratch.

224
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:54,273
Oh, you kids, always getting
yourselves into trouble.

225
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:56,567
[inhales] Hold on.
I have just the medicine for you.

226
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:58,986
Uh, Doc…

227
00:13:03,365 --> 00:13:04,950
[Teresa] Here.

228
00:13:05,034 --> 00:13:07,286
Apply this regularly on your wound, okay?

229
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:10,331
Always apply it so that…

230
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,541
it heals quickly.

231
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:15,794
It's such a shame to stain
your handsome face.

232
00:13:15,878 --> 00:13:17,296
Here, take it.

233
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:20,799
I use that same ointment
with Marcus's wounds too.

234
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:24,303
That's why, despite his job,

235
00:13:24,386 --> 00:13:27,765
my baby's face is still
as handsome as ever.

236
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:28,682
[both chuckles]

237
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:31,352
Thank you.

238
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:33,896
Well, then. Let's eat.

239
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,523
- [Teresa] Come on.
- [Espina] Okay.

240
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:36,690
This way.

241
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:44,907
When do you plan
to tell me about this, Lara?

242
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:47,117
All along,

243
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:49,787
Datu Rahman is in Marcus' hands,

244
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:55,292
and you didn't even bother
telling me about it!

245
00:13:55,376 --> 00:13:56,502
[tense music playing]

246
00:13:56,585 --> 00:13:58,003
[breathes sharply]

247
00:13:58,087 --> 00:14:00,047
I was gonna tell you, Dad, but, um..

248
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:02,591
I didn't tell you just yet
because I'm still trying to resolve it.

249
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:03,968
[Carillo] Oh!

250
00:14:04,051 --> 00:14:08,514
Lara, it's not your job to resolve things!

251
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:14,687
Your responsibility is to control
the situation, Lara,

252
00:14:14,770 --> 00:14:16,981
which is what you're lacking right now!

253
00:14:17,064 --> 00:14:19,316
You're losing control!

254
00:14:21,235 --> 00:14:24,697
I even got you to become a part of SID,

255
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:29,660
and yet you couldn't even
control your own teammate!

256
00:14:29,743 --> 00:14:33,038
[tense music playing]

257
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:36,792
I almost got Datu Rahman,
but his son, Jalil Abubakar,

258
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,836
beat me to it.

259
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:40,379
Almost…

260
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:45,801
[scoffs, in English] That makes it
even more disappointing, Lara.

261
00:14:47,386 --> 00:14:51,265
Almost is not enough

262
00:14:51,348 --> 00:14:54,435
to win a war!

263
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:58,689
Almost! Almost! How foolish!

264
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,401
[in English] Look.

265
00:15:02,484 --> 00:15:04,361
Look at what's happening, Lara.

266
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:08,699
Datu Rahman

267
00:15:08,782 --> 00:15:11,201
is in Mustapha's hands!

268
00:15:11,285 --> 00:15:16,749
Just imagine the things
he'll hear from Datu Rahman!

269
00:15:16,832 --> 00:15:21,879
[music intensifies]

270
00:15:29,011 --> 00:15:33,057
[gentle music playing]

271
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:39,146
It's as if

272
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:40,689
an angel passed by.

273
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:43,025
[Marcus scoffs]

274
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:45,152
It's because you prepared so much, Ma.

275
00:15:45,235 --> 00:15:46,946
- This is a feast!
- [chuckles]

276
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,198
- [Marcus] It's delicious!
- Mm-hmm. All of it is good.

277
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:53,911
Of course it is because I know that

278
00:15:53,994 --> 00:15:56,080
these are your favorites.

279
00:15:59,083 --> 00:15:59,917
[Teresa sighs]

280
00:16:05,255 --> 00:16:06,382
Are you alright, Ma?

281
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:11,053
[Teresa sobbing]

282
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:13,347
I'm just so happy because it's like…

283
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:18,602
it's been so long
since we had a meal together.

284
00:16:18,686 --> 00:16:19,645
[sniffles]

285
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:26,443
Don't mind me. Go ahead.
Just continue eating.

286
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:30,447
[melancholic music playing]

287
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:32,032
[Teresa] Go on. Don't mind me.

288
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:35,869
[Teresa sighs, sniffles]

289
00:16:35,953 --> 00:16:37,955
- Eat a lot.
- Thank you.

290
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:15,159
[somber music playing]

291
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:16,285
[Jamilah] Hm?

292
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:19,830
Sitti?

293
00:17:19,913 --> 00:17:23,000
I can't sleep, Jamilah.

294
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:27,254
Why? Do you feel uncomfortable?

295
00:17:27,337 --> 00:17:31,842
It's because I can't hear
the sound of the waves crashing.

296
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:34,845
[sighs] Oh…

297
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:38,265
This area is far from the sea.

298
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:42,269
Do you miss our island?

299
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:44,605
[melancholic music playing]

300
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:48,275
Come here. I'll get you to sleep soundly.

301
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:59,995
[Jamilah]
♪ <i>There are two little children</i> ♪

302
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:04,041
♪ <i>Sitting together in a boat</i> ♪

303
00:18:04,124 --> 00:18:08,378
♪ <i>There is only a picture of them</i> ♪

304
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:11,924
♪ <i>Yet it makes me smile</i> ♪

305
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:16,553
♪ <i>The two little children</i> ♪

306
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:20,474
♪ <i>Where might they be going?</i> ♪

307
00:18:20,557 --> 00:18:24,478
♪ <i>Their smiles and laughter</i> ♪

308
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:29,775
♪ <i>They show no sign of weakness</i> ♪

309
00:18:29,858 --> 00:18:33,487
♪ <i>Across the vast and open ocean</i> ♪

310
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:37,366
♪ <i>Far from forests, beyond the waves</i> ♪

311
00:18:37,449 --> 00:18:41,370
♪ <i>Upon the clear waters</i> ♪

312
00:18:41,453 --> 00:18:46,333
♪ <i>Beneath the warmth of the sun</i> ♪

313
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:53,173
[gentle music playing]

314
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:17,364
[pensive music playing]

315
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:25,038
[Teresa] <i>What happened to your face?</i>

316
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:28,208
Ah… It's nothing. Just a scratch.

317
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,127
Hold on. I have just the medicine for you.

318
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:32,337
Uh… Doc.

319
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:34,298
Apply this regularly on your wound, okay?

320
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:36,717
So that it heals quickly.

321
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:42,472
[Teresa] <i>I'm just reminded</i>
<i>of my other son.</i>

322
00:19:42,973 --> 00:19:44,600
<i>Gabriel.</i>

323
00:19:45,809 --> 00:19:47,436
He was my youngest. [sniffles]

324
00:19:48,395 --> 00:19:50,314
He went missing a long time ago.

325
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:53,650
It's been 30 years.

326
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:56,862
Sometimes I wonder why
he was the one who disappeared.

327
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:00,240
They should've taken me instead, you know?

328
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,492
But I decided

329
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:04,620
that my life needs to have meaning,

330
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,915
<i>so that losing my brother</i>
<i>won't be in vain.</i>

331
00:20:09,374 --> 00:20:11,752
[Teresa] <i>I'm just so happy because…</i>

332
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:15,464
it's been so long since
our dining table felt this complete.

333
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:16,381
[sniffles]

334
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:21,511
Marcus's brother went missing.

335
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:24,681
I'm adopted.

336
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:29,102
What if I'm actually Gabriel?

337
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:37,653
[pensive music continues]

338
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:40,697
Impossible.

339
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:43,116
He's dead.

340
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:45,118
[chuckles]

341
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:52,084
[exhales deeply]

342
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,466
Reyes.

343
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:01,009
- Reyes.
- What?

344
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,803
When are we having that dinner again?

345
00:21:02,886 --> 00:21:04,805
I already miss Doctor Teresa's cooking.

346
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,432
Don't you have food at your own place?

347
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:11,770
Do you need a mother too?

348
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:13,313
[Ethan] Sir! Sir!

349
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:14,523
Sir Marcus!

350
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:18,110
I've traced the IP address
of the user account "Uncle Tony."

351
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:21,905
[stirring music playing]

352
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:24,408
[sirens wailing]

353
00:21:26,034 --> 00:21:26,827
[Marcus] Move.

354
00:21:26,910 --> 00:21:29,329
[suspenseful music playing]

355
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:31,039
[Espina] Clear.

356
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:46,305
Sir!

357
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:48,265
Sir Marcus!

358
00:21:48,348 --> 00:21:52,769
[suspenseful music continues]

359
00:21:58,942 --> 00:22:00,986
Rodriguez! Check his pulse.

360
00:22:12,289 --> 00:22:13,999
This wasn't a suicide.

361
00:22:14,082 --> 00:22:20,505
[unsettling music playing]

362
00:22:26,219 --> 00:22:30,140
<i>The owner of the gaming shop,</i>
<i>identified as Polly Santiago,</i>

363
00:22:30,223 --> 00:22:31,725
<i>has been found dead.</i>

364
00:22:31,808 --> 00:22:37,147
<i>Santiago was believed to be</i>
<i>behind the "Uncle Tony" account</i>

365
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:39,733
<i>on Cubix, a popular platform</i>

366
00:22:39,816 --> 00:22:43,487
<i>where illegal firearms are being traded.</i>

367
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:46,573
<i>Although the primary suspect</i>
<i>have died by suicide,</i>

368
00:22:46,656 --> 00:22:49,284
<i>authorities still consider this</i>
<i>a major blow</i>

369
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:52,412
<i>to online gun trafficking in the country.</i>

370
00:22:52,496 --> 00:22:58,126
<i>With Task Force Alpha's</i>
<i>successful rescue of students</i>

371
00:22:58,210 --> 00:23:02,672
<i>from East Valley Montessori</i>
<i>and other youths</i>

372
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:04,841
<i>from illegal syndicates,</i>

373
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:09,638
<i>public trust in law enforcement</i>
<i>appears to be returning.</i>

374
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:12,766
<i>An investment deal between</i>
<i>the Philippines and Japan</i>

375
00:23:12,849 --> 00:23:15,185
<i>is also set to push through,</i>

376
00:23:15,268 --> 00:23:19,523
<i>which could significantly</i>
<i>boost the country's economy.</i>

377
00:23:20,315 --> 00:23:22,901
They did the same thing
to Colonel Del Mundo.

378
00:23:22,984 --> 00:23:24,444
They always get ahead of us.

379
00:23:25,028 --> 00:23:27,197
They're used to silencing people.

380
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:32,119
[unsettling music playing]

381
00:23:49,386 --> 00:23:50,929
- [Marcus] Sir.
- [Jalil] Sir.

382
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:54,266
[in English] Agent Reyes. Goddammit!

383
00:23:54,349 --> 00:23:55,684
Sir, what's going on?

384
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:56,893
[Usman] Buddy.

385
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:06,111
[unsettling music continues]

386
00:24:28,049 --> 00:24:32,637
Because of that video,
your position and your life are in danger!

387
00:24:32,721 --> 00:24:36,016
Sir, whoever uploaded that video
has deep resources.

388
00:24:36,099 --> 00:24:38,059
[Marcus] <i>They're the ones sabotaging us.</i>

389
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:40,812
And as TFA,
we're supposed to stand by him.

390
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:43,064
You guys are really like dogs.

391
00:24:43,148 --> 00:24:44,983
So loyal.

392
00:24:45,066 --> 00:24:46,318
[Espina] They uploaded that video

393
00:24:46,401 --> 00:24:47,986
because Marcus is a major threat to them.

394
00:24:48,069 --> 00:24:48,945
We need to do something.

395
00:24:49,613 --> 00:24:51,531
[Espina] <i>You won't be able to help Marcus.</i>

396
00:24:52,115 --> 00:24:53,658
The video is real.

397
00:24:53,742 --> 00:24:56,995
I know your son is not a bad person.

398
00:24:57,078 --> 00:24:58,580
[Lara, in English]
<i>We're supposed to be a team.</i>

399
00:24:58,663 --> 00:25:01,583
But I can't even help you
because you never tell me anything!

400
00:25:01,666 --> 00:25:04,878
Because I don't trust anyone
here right now, Lara.

401
00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:06,379
[Lara, in English] <i>Even me?</i>

402
00:25:06,463 --> 00:25:09,883
[Carillo] <i>You still haven't arrested</i>
<i>Marcus Reyes.</i>

403
00:25:09,966 --> 00:25:12,719
I thought you were competent?

404
00:25:12,802 --> 00:25:17,057
Why are you so certain
Agent Reyes is guilty?

405
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:19,142
[Felix] <i>Get along with Task Force Alpha</i>

406
00:25:19,226 --> 00:25:21,311
<i>because they're the ones</i>
<i>you need to manipulate.</i>
